'''Igor Vladimirovich Sergeev''' ({{langx|ru|Игорь Владимирович Сергеев}}; born 30 April 1993) is an Uzbek professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] in the [[Persian Gulf Pro League]] and the [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan national team]].

==Club career==

=== Pakhtakor ===
Sergeev made his [[Uzbek League]] debut for [[Pakhtakor Tashkent FK|Pakhtakor Tashkent]] on 5 March 2011 against [[Qizilqum Zarafshon]] at the [[Pakhtakor Markaziy Stadium]] coming on as a 90th-minute substitute for Temurkhuja Abdukholikov as Tashkent won the match 2–0.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pakhtakor 2-0 Qizilqum|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2011/03/05/uzbekistan/pfl/pakhtakor-tashkent/qizilqum-zarafshon/1059376/|work=Soccerway|access-date=20 November 2012}}</ref>

==== Beijing Guoan (loan) ====
On 6 July 2016, Sergeev was loaned to [[Chinese Super League]] club [[Beijing Guoan F.C.|Beijing Guoan]] joining his national team teammate [[Egor Krimets]]. On 16 October, he received his first goal during 2016 season in the match against [[Changchun Yatai F.C.|Changchun Yatai]].

=== Return to Pakhtakor ===
On 6 July 2018, Sergeev returned to [[Pakhtakor Tashkent FK|Pakhtakor Tashkent]].<ref>{{cite web |title=ИГОРЬ СЕРГЕЕВ ВЕРНУЛСЯ В ПАХТАКОР |url=http://www.pakhtakor.uz/news/cnews/2397 |website=pakhtakor.uz |publisher=Pakhtakor Tashkent |access-date=23 August 2018 |language=ru |date=6 July 2018}}</ref>

===Aktobe===
On 18 February 2021, [[FC Aktobe]] announced the signings of Sergeev.<ref>{{cite web |title=Игорь Сергеев - "Ақтөбе" футбол клубының ойыншысы! |url=https://vk.com/wall-64832061_138171 |website=vk.com |publisher=FC Aktobe VK |access-date=18 February 2021 |language=Russian |date=18 February 2021}}</ref>

===Tobol===
On 19 July 2021, Sergeev left Aktobe to sign for [[FC Tobol|Tobol]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Игорь Сергеев – игрок Тобола |url=https://fctobol.kz/igor-sergeev-igrok-tobola/ |website=fctobol.kz/ |publisher=FC Tobol |access-date=19 July 2021 |language=Russian |date=19 July 2021 |archive-date=19 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210719091416/https://fctobol.kz/igor-sergeev-igrok-tobola/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> 
On 29 July 2021, during a [[2021–22 UEFA Europa Conference League qualifying phase and play-off round|2021–22 UEFA Europa Conference League 2nd qualifying round]] game, he scored a brace against [[HNK Hajduk Split|Hajduk Split]], becoming the first Uzbek to score in the [[UEFA Conference League]].<ref>{{cite web |title=History: Topol 4-1 Hajduk Split |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaconferenceleague/match/2032908/ |website=UEFA |access-date=4 February 2025}}</ref> Though his countryman [[Eldor Shomurodov]] scored three weeks later, Sergeev remains at 28 years the oldest Uzbek goalscorer in the competition.<ref>{{cite web |title=History: Trabzonspor 1-2 Roma |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaconferenceleague/match/2033139--trabzonspor-vs-roma/ |website=UEFA |access-date=4 February 2025}}</ref> On 8 June 2023, Sergeev left Tobol by mutual consent.<ref>{{cite web |title=Спасибо, Игорь! |url=https://fctobol.kz/2023/06/08/%d1%81%d0%bf%d0%b0%d1%81%d0%b8%d0%b1%d0%be-%d0%b8%d0%b3%d0%be%d1%80%d1%8c/ |website=fctobol.kz |publisher=FC Tobol |access-date=8 June 2023 |language=Russian |date=8 June 2023}}</ref>

===BG Pathum United===
On 13 June 2023, [[BG Pathum United F.C.|BG Pathum United]] announced the signing of Sergeev.<ref>{{cite web |title=HERE COMES NEW CHALLENGE |url=https://www.facebook.com/BGPATHUMUNITED/videos/218868084408713|publisher=BG Pathum United |access-date=13 June 2023 |language=th |date=19 June 2023}}</ref>

=== Second Pakhtakor return ===
On 25 December 2024, [[Pakhtakor FC|Pakhtakor]] announced the return of Sergeev from [[BG Pathum United F.C.|BG Pathum United]] to a one-year contract.<ref name="Igor Sergeev">{{cite web |title=Игорь Сергеев "Пахтакор"га қайтди |url=http://www.pakhtakor.uz/news/cnews/7266 |website=pakhtakor.uz |publisher=Pakhtakor FC |access-date=9 January 2025 |language=Uzbek |date=25 December 2024}}</ref>

=== Persepolis F.C. ===

4 January 2026: He accepted Persepolis’ offer and came to Iran. Despite an offer from [[Sepahan S.C.|Sepahan]], he chose Iran’s most popular team, [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=رسمی: اولین خرید پرسپولیس در راه تهران |url=https://www.varzesh3.com/news/2235991/%D9%81%D9%88%D8%B1%DB%8C-%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%88%D9%84%DB%8C%D9%86-%D8%AE%D8%B1%DB%8C%D8%AF-%D9%BE%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%BE%D9%88%D9%84%DB%8C%D8%B3-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%AA%D9%87%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86 |access-date=2026-01-03 |website=ورزش سه |language=fa}}</ref>

==International career==
Sergeev had established himself as a regular at the [[Uzbekistan national under-20 football team|under-20]] level for Uzbekistan. After the [[2012 AFC U-19 Championship]] Sergeev came out as the top scorer of the tournament with 7 goals throughout as he led Uzbekistan's U20s to the semi-finals, where they lost to [[South Korea national under-20 football team|South Korea U20s]] 3–1.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sergeev scoops top scorer award|url=http://www.the-afc.com/en/tournaments/men-a-youth/afc-u19-championship/40578-top-scorer|work=The Asian Football Confederation|access-date=20 November 2012|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121121014228/http://www.the-afc.com/en/tournaments/men-a-youth/afc-u19-championship/40578-top-scorer|archive-date=21 November 2012}}</ref>

He made his debut for main team, [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan]] on 10 September 2013 in [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC fifth round|2014 FIFA World Cup qualification]] match against [[Jordan national football team|Jordan]]. He was named in Uzbekistan's squad for [[2015 AFC Asian Cup]], held in Australia. Sergeev played three matches and scored Uzbekistan's 1–0 winning goal against [[North Korea national football team|North Korea]] in their opening match in Group B. Sergeev performance with BG Pathum United earn him a call-up to the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]] held in Qatar.

